If the consumer is the employer of record, the consumer's roles and responsibilities shall include but not be limited to the following:
Developing a job description;
Selecting providers and submitting information for any required background screening;
With assistance of the cabinet or its agents, developing a person-centered plan and communicating needs, preferences, and expectations about services being purchased;
Providing the fiscal intermediary with all information necessary for provider payments and tax requirements; and
Ending the employment of an unsatisfactory provider.

The roles and responsibilities of the cabinet or its agents shall include but not be limited to the following:
Assessing each consumer's functional needs, helping with the development of a person-centered plan, and providing ongoing assistance with the plan;
Offering the services of service advisors who shall provide training, technical assistance, and support to the consumer as prescribed through an administrative regulation promulgated by the cabinet in accordance with KRS Chapter 13A;
Approving fiscal intermediaries; and
Establishing the minimum qualifications for all providers and being the final arbiter of the fitness of any individual to be a provider.
